description: Expo + Convex stack boundaries and workflow for Agree on a Time
alwaysApply: true
---

# Stack and layout

- **Client app:** Expo (SDK 54+) with **Expo Router** under `app/`. Use file-based routes; `@/` path alias maps to the repo root.
- **UI:** React Native + **NativeWind** (`className`). Reuse patterns from existing screens (e.g. `app/sign-in.tsx`, tabs).
- **Shared client code:** `lib/`, `hooks/`, `components/`.
- **Backend:** **Convex only** — `convex/` for schema, queries, mutations, actions, HTTP (`http.ts`), auth wiring. No Next.js API routes, no `app/` “server components”, no Drizzle/Neon/Postgres in this repo.

# Commands

- Prefer **`pnpm lint`** and **`pnpm exec tsc --noEmit`** before treating a change as complete.
- Convex: **`pnpm convex:dev`** links deployment and regenerates `convex/_generated/`; do not assume `_generated` exists in a fresh clone until codegen has run.

# Issues and branches

- Use **task branches** off `main` (e.g. `feature/dev-###-short-name`). Do not land unrelated work on `main` without a PR.
- When work maps to Linear, reference **`DEV-###`** in commit messages and **update Linear status** when starting, finishing review, and merging.
- After commits exist on a task branch, **push to `origin` and open a PR to `main`** (GitHub CLI when available). Follow `.cursor/rules/git-push-and-pr.mdc`.

# Accessibility (baseline)

- Interactive controls need meaningful **`accessibilityLabel`** (and `accessibilityRole` where helpful). Favor patterns already used on auth and tab screens.
